<br>
1)  They can handle multiple mobs much better (Point in fact you can kill 3 specters at once at level 40)<br>
<br>
2)  They are much better at escaping death.  Not really due to feign death, but instead harmshield.<br>
<br>
3)  They get the wizard's entire line of defensive skins (this is totally unfair).<br>
<br>
Some points for the magi:<br>
<br>
1)  Best damage shields in the game.<br>
<br>
2)  By far the best pets (Especially from 16-44, I haven't played post fifty).<br>
<br>
3)  Less luck-factor in battles.  After the speed nerf necro pets can die relatively easily ala enchanter pets.  Fear has a recycle time and if it is resisted sometimes as little as once it can turn into you running for it.  The more mobs the more likely fear will resist and you will die.<br>
<br>
4)  The Darkness line looks good, but in truth it is very resistable and not much better than most DDs for it's damage.<br>
<br>
A couple misconceptions about necromancers:<br>
<br>
1)  Feign death is not so great, especially after 35.  The skill constantly improves the spell is always the same, and fails frequently.<br>
<br>
2)  Necros are very group friendly simply because they bring that power to the group.  However they are not group friendly in the sense that more necros means less power (since nothing stacks including the 44 DD).<br>
